GPUVerify: COMMAND_LINE_ERROR error (1): too few arguments
root@1cf92638093f:/home/gv/gpuverify/InvariantGenerationBenchmarks# gpuverify --help
usage: gpuverify [options] <kernel>

GPUVerify frontend

positional arguments:
  kernel                Kernel file to verify

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit

GENERAL OPTIONS:
  --version             Show version information and exit
  -D <value>            Define symbol
  -I <value>            Add directory to include search path
  --findbugs            Run tool in bug-finding mode
  --verify              Run tool in verification mode
  --loop-unwind= X      Explore traces that pass through at most X loop heads.
                        Implies --findbugs
  --check-array-bounds  Enable checking for any array out-of-bounds access
  --no-benign-tolerance
                        Do not tolerate benign data races
  --only-divergence     Only check for barrier divergence, not races
  --only-intra-group    Do not check for inter-group races
  --verbose             Show subcommands and use verbose output
  --silent              Silent on success; only show errors/timing
  --time                Show timing information
  --time-as-csv= X      Print timing information as CSV with label X
  --timeout= X          Allow each component to run for at most X seconds. A
                        timeout of 0 disables the timeout. The default is 300s
  --opencl              Assume the kernel is an OpenCL kernel
  --cuda                Assume the kernel is a CUDA kernel

SIZING:
  Define the dimensionality and size of each dimension as a 1-, 2-, or
  3-tuple, optionally wrapped in []. For example, [1,2] or 2,3,4. Use * for
  an unconstrained value

  --local_size= GROUP_SIZE
                        Specify the dimensions of an OpenCL work-group. This
                        corresponds to the 'local_work_size' parameter of
                        'clEnqueueNDRangeKernel'.
  --global_size= GLOBAL_SIZE
                        Specify dimensions of the OpenCL NDRange. This
                        corresponds to the 'global_work_size' parameter of
                        'clEnqueueNDRangeKernel'. Mutually exclusive with
                        --num_groups
  --num_groups= NUM_GROUPS
                        Specify the dimensions of a grid of OpenCL work-
                        groups. Mutually exclusive with --global_size
  --global_offset= GLOBAL_OFFSET
                        Specify the OpenCL global offset. This corresponds to
                        the 'global_offset' parameter of
                        'clEnqueueNDRangeKernel'.
  --blockDim= GROUP_SIZE
                        Specify the CUDA thread block size
  --gridDim= NUM_GROUPS
                        Specify the CUDA grid size

ADVANCED OPTIONS:
  --pointer-bitwidth= {32,64}
                        Set the pointer bitwidth. The default is 32
  --adversarial-abstraction
                        Abstract shared state, so that reads are non-
                        deterministic
  --equality-abstraction
                        At barriers, make shared arrays non-deterministic but
                        consistent between threads
  --asymmetric-asserts  Emit assertions only for the first thread. Sound, and
                        may lead to faster verification, but can yield false
                        positives
  --boogie-file= X.bpl  Specify a supporting .bpl file to be used during
                        verification
  --math-int            Represent integer types using mathematical integers
                        instead of bit-vectors
  --no-annotations      Ignore all source-level annotations
  --only-requires       Ignore all source-level annotations except for
                        requires
  --invariants-as-candidates
                        Interpret all source-level invariants as candidates
  --no-barrier-access-checks
                        Turn off access checks for barrier invariants
  --no-inline           Turn off automatic function inlining
  --only-log            Log accesses to arrays, but do not check for races.
                        This can be useful for determining access pattern
                        invariants
  --kernel-args= K,v1,...,vn
                        For kernel K with scalar parameters x1, ..., xn, add
                        the preconditions x1 == v1, ..., xn == vn. Use * to
                        denote an unconstrained parameter
  --kernel-arrays= K,s1,...,sn
                        For kernel K with array parameters p1, ..., pn, assume
                        that sizeof(p1) == s1, ... sizeof(pn) == sn. Use * to
                        denote an unconstrained size
  --warp-sync= X        Synchronize threads within warps of size X.
  --race-instrumenter= {original,watchdog-single,watchdog-multiple}
                        Choose which method of race instrumentation to use.
                        The default is watchdog-single
  --solver= {z3,cvc4}   Select the SMT solver to use as backend. Default is z3
  --stop-at-opt         Stop after LLVM optimization pass
  --stop-at-gbpl        Stop after generating gbpl file
  --stop-at-bpl         Stop after generating bpl file
  --stop-at-cbpl        Stop after generating an annotated bpl file

DEVELOPMENT OPTIONS:
  --debug               Enable debugging of GPUVerify components: exceptions
                        will not be suppressed
  --keep-temps          Keep the intermediate bc, gbpl, and cbpl files
  --gen-smt2            Generate an smt2 file
  --clang-opt= CLANG_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to Clang
  --opt-opt= OPT_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to the LLVM optimization
                        pass
  --bugle-opt= BUGLE_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to Bugle
  --vcgen-opt= VCGEN_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to VC generator
  --cruncher-opt= CRUNCHER_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to the cruncher
  --boogie-opt= BOOGIE_OPTIONS
                        Specify option to be passed to Boogie

INVARIANT INFERENCE OPTIONS:
  --no-infer            Turn off invariant inference
  --omit-infer= X       Do not generate invariants of type 'X'
  --infer-info          Prints information about the invariant inference
                        process
  --k-induction-depth= X
                        Applies k-induction with k=X to all loops

JSON MODE:
  --json                The kernels to be verified are specified through a
                        JSON file
  --list-intercepted    List the kernels specified in the JSON file
  --verify-intercepted= X
                        Verify kernel 'X' from the JSON file
  --verify-all-intercepted
                        Verify all the kernels from the JSON file
  --cache= X            Use 'X' as result cache
